##  In printf() what does the format option %2.5f mean? 
format a float with at least 2 characters wide before decimal point and 5 characters long after the decimal point.
##  In printf() what does the format option %s, %f, %c, %d mean? 
s - format a string of characters 
f - format a float
c - format a character
d - format a integer aka decimal.

